<div class="card">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h1 class="card-title mb-4">About Winnipeg Tree Explorer</h1>

    <p>
      Winnipeg Tree Explorer is a Ruby on Rails application that allows users to explore
      the City of Winnipeg Tree Inventory dataset. The dataset contains detailed information
      about trees located throughout the city, including species, size, and location data.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-4">Dataset</h2>
    <p>The data used in this application comes from the City of Winnipeg Open Data portal. It includes information such as:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Common and botanical tree names</li>
      <li>Tree size (diameter at breast height)</li>
      <li>Neighbourhood and electoral ward</li>
      <li>Site and location details</li>
      <li>Geographic coordinates</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-4">Database Structure</h2>
    <p>The application uses three related tables to organize the data:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Neighbourhoods</strong> – stores neighbourhood names and electoral wards</li>
      <li><strong>Sites</strong> – stores location details and belongs to a neighbourhood</li>
      <li><strong>Trees</strong> – stores tree-specific data and belongs to a site</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      A neighbourhood has many sites, and a site has many trees. This structure allows
      the application to display hierarchical relationships between data and supports
      navigation from trees to their associated sites and neighbourhoods.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-4">Entity Relationship Diagram</h2>

    <%= image_tag "ERD.png", alt: "Entity Relationship Diagram", class: "img-fluid border rounded" %>
  </div>
</div>